article.headline: Davidson 83, Furman 43
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Stephen Curry scored 30 points and Davidson remained undefeated in the Southern Conference by beating Furman 83-43 on Wednesday night. Will Archambault added 13 points for the Wildcats (15-3, 8-0), who led by as many as 49 points. It was Davidson's most lopsided victory of the season, surpassing its 35-point win over James Madison in the Wildcats' second game of the season. It was also the Paladins' most-lopsided loss this season, worse than a 27-point loss to Chattanooga on Jan. 10. Curry, the nation's leading scorer at 29.1 points per game, also had five assists and five steals for Davidson, which held the Paladins (2-14, 0-7) to 32 percent shooting (15 of 47) and forced them into 22 turnovers. Justin Dehm scored 12 points for Furman, which lost its sixth straight game and 14 of its last 15.
